                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                <head>No. 825.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Whitehouse</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 17, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>,<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé, Mexico:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Major Oswald H. Ernst, detailed to visit El Paso, will probably start hence
                    Monday. Express satisfaction at promised Mexican co-operation and request proper
                    facilities for Major Ernst.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
